iousness/dp/938624232X|title=Hard Talk: A Discourse on Political Consciuosness|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Vishwabharati Research Centre|year=2017|isbn=978-9386242327|location=India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|title=IN LOVE WITH COSMOS: A WORK OF SPIRITUALITY AND COSMIC CULTURE|publisher=Earth Vision Publications|year=2017|isbn=9789384922436|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=|translator-last=Mohammadi|translator-first=Nargues}}\n*{{Cite book|title=MASTERS OF CREATIVE IMPULSE: MOST VIBRANT VOICES FROM CONTEMPORARY INDIAN ENGLISH POETRY|publisher=VISHWABHARATI AND THEMATICS INDOTECH|year=2017|isbn=9789386242518|editor-last=ANAND|editor-first=MANMINDER SINGH ANAND|location=NEW DELHI INDIA|pages=|editor-last2=Rathore|editor-first2=M A}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|title=GEET UNSUNG SONG OF ETERNITY: A SEQUEL TO JOHN MILTON'S 'PARADISE LOST' (2ND ED.)|publisher=Aditya Prakashan In Association With Vishwabharati Research Centre|year=2018|isbn=9789387651883|location=New Delhi India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/The_Ganturbury_Tales.html?id=In8-ygEACAAJ&redir_esc=y|title=THE GANTURBURY TALES: A SEQUEL TO GEOFFREY CHAUCER'S 'THE CANTERBURY TALES'|publisher=Authorpress|year=2018|isbn=9789388008938|location=New Delhi India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Anand|first=J S|date=2018-02-24|title=POETIC CREATION AND RECREATION: THE MAGIC SPELL AND THE CLOUD SYNDROME|url=|journal=International Seminar on Novel Issues in Indian Writing in English|publisher=Authorpress|publication-place=New Delhi India|volume=|pages=53-57|isbn=9789387651166|via=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/Satanic-Empire-Jernail-Singh-Anand/dp/9383755997|title=The Satanic Empire|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755998|location=Gurgaon Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|title=VOICES FROM THE VOID|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755875|location=Gurgaon Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|title=PAN INDIAN POETRY IN ENGLISH SPANNING FIRST TWO DECADES OF 21ST CENTURY|publisher=Today and Tomorrow's Printers and Publishers|year=2019|isbn=9788170196495|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=New Delhi India|pages=|editor-last2=Chakraborti|editor-first2=Basudeb}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/FIGHTING-FLAMES-Dr-J-Anand/dp/9383755830|title=FIGHTING THE FLAMES|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755837|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/BROKEN-NARRATIVE-JERNAIL-SINGH-ANAND/dp/B0849T7ZCW/ref=sr_1_6?qid=1585744205&refinements=p_27%3ADr+Jernail+Singh+Anand&s=books&sr=1-6|title=The Broken Narrative|publisher=YAYATI MADAN G GANDHI GROUP OF PUBLICATION|year=2020|isbn=9788194485827|location=Hisar Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|title=LILACS IN BLOOM|publisher=The Poetry Society of India|others=A Project of Galaxy International Foundation|year=2020|isbn=9789389213133|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=Hisar Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|title=POETS & POETRY: SPACES WITHIN & WITHOUT|publisher=Earth Vision Publications|year=2020|isbn=9788194485841|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=|editor-last2=Jaggi|editor-first2=Parneet}}\n*{{Cite book|title=DYNAMICS OF POETRY: THE SAID AND THE UNSAID|publisher=Earth Vision Publication|year=2020|isbn=9788194485872|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=|editor-last2=Jaggi|editor-first2=Parneet}}\n\n==Major awards and recognition==\n*Member of the Commission for the International Best Poet Award 2017 of the World Nations Writers Union, Kazakhstan<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnwu.org/index.php/en/|title=High Level Officials of THE WORLD NATION WRITERS UNION OF KAZAKHSTAN (WNWU)|last=Garrido|first=Carlos Hugo|date=2017-10-09|website=World Nation Writers' Union|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-07-12}}</ref>\n*First Ambassador of the World Union of Poets, Italy. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/04/25/world-union-of-poets-celebrates-the-power-of-poetry-aims-to-bring-a-revolution-in-the-consciousness-of-time-issued-by-dr-j-s-anand-ambassador-and-general-director-wup/|title=WORLD UNION OF POETS CELEBRATES THE POWER OF POETRY: AIMS TO BRING A REVOLUTION IN THE CONSCIOUSNESS OF TIME, ISSUED BY Dr. J.S. ANAND, AMBASSADOR AND GENERAL DIRECTOR WUP|last=BORTOLAZZI|first=SILVANO|date=2016-04-25|website=ATUNIS|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n*Chairperson of World Foundation for Peace, and Writers International Foundation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/bathinda/poems-rediscover-island-called-self/216121.html|title=Poems rediscover \u2018island called self\u2019|date=1 April 2016|website=The Tribune}}</ref>\n*Dr Anand  evolved the theory of BIOTEXT in Literary Theory<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2017/10/11/j-s-anands-theory-of-biotext-and-critical-perspectives-on-his-poetic-and-spiritual-creed-first-edition-2016-by-dr-roghayeh-farsi-author-introduction/|title=J.S. Anand\u2019s Theory of Biotext And Critical Perspectives on His Poetic and Spiritual Creed (First Edition, 2016) /  By Dr Roghayeh Farsi (Author, Introduction)|date=2017-10-11|work=Galaktika Poetike  \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref>\n*Cross for Peace for his Lifetime Achievement in the Field of Poetry and Peace by Wolrd Union of Poets. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/11-May-2016/pak-poet-to-get-cross-for-peace-award|title=Pak poet to get Cross for Peace Award|last=Ahmad|first=Israr|date=2016-05-11|website=The Nation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n*2017: Art4peace award by Art4peace Foundation, Hollywood, USA\n*2017: World epitome of leadership award World Institute of Peace, Nigeria\n*2017: Honored with Lord of World Peace and Literature Award, conferred at India World Poetry Festival, held at Ramoji City, Hyderabad 13-14th Oct, 2017\n*Dr M S Randhawa Award for Promotion of Art & Culture of Punjab Conferred\n*2009: Recipient of Penguin Rising Personalities of India Award \n*2008: Best Educationist Award for the outstanding achievements in academics by National and International Compendium in New Delhi\n*Avantika educational excellence award by Sri Rajiv Gandhi Foundation Ratia\n*Founder President, Philosophique Poetica [De-Anand] - A Portal for Poetry, Art, Peace and Philosophy\n\n==Membership and appointments==\n*Member, Syndicate, Punjabi University, Patiala.\n*Fellow, Punjabi University, Patiala\n*Member, Board of Studies, Guru Kashi University, Talwandi Sabo\n*National Vice-president, International Human Rights Observatory [ihro]\n*Patron and Honorary Chief Editor: Symphony International \n*Life Member: [[United Writers' Association|United Writers Association]], Chennai\t\n*Chairman of the International Society of Poets\t\n*Chairman of the Sufi Arts Foundation\t\n*Member of the Association of Indian College Principals\t\n*Patron: Academic Earth Institute of Multi-studies\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anand, Jernail Singh}}\n[[Category:Poets from Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=June 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Jernail Singh Anand\n| image         = [[File:Jernail Singh Poet.png|250px]]\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = 1955\n| birth_place   = Ludhiana, Punjab \n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Poet, author, philosopher, spiritualist\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n\n'''Jernail Singh Anand''' is a poet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://jamiededes.com/2017/10/19/dr-jernail-s-anand-poet-writing-in-the-virtual-world-by-aprilia-zank-ph-d/|title=\"Dr. Jernail S. Anand (Poet), Writing in the Virtual World\" by Aprilia Zank, Ph.D.|date=2017-10-19|work=THE POET BY DAY|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://verbumlandiart.com/dr-jernail-singh-anand-a-philosopher-of-language-life-and-literature-essay-of-italian-poetess-claudia-piccinno/|title=Dr JERNAIL SINGH ANAND \u2026.a philosopher of Language Life and Literature / Essay of Italian poetess Claudia Piccinno \u2013 VERBUMLANDIART|website=verbumlandiof Maharaja Ranjit Singh College, art.com|language=it-IT|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> Anand has authored 65 books of English Poetry, fiction, [[non-fiction]] and spirituality.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/09/14/dr-jernail-s-anand/|title=Dr. Jernail S. ANAND|date=2016-09-14|work=Galaktika Poetike  \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bol.com/nl/p/a-million-destinies/9200000014175757/|title= A Million Destinies [Poems], Dr Jernail Singh Anand {{!}} 9781484831342 {{!}} Boeken|website=www.bol.com|language=nl-NL|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> He was awarded a Ph. D. in English by Panjab University Chandigarh  in year 2000. He is a environmentalist and a column writer. He retired as Principal and is now on an Honorary Position of Professor Emeritus at Institute of European Roma Studies and Research, Crimes Against Humanity and International Law, Belgrade, Serbia. Dr Anand has co-innovated the theory of Bio-Text in Critical Theory along with an Iranian Scholar, Dr Roghaye Farsi. He Was President of The World Poetry Conference Organized in October 2019 in Bathinda Punjab, India. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Dayal,|first=Dr Deen|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dxlgDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT655&lpg=PT655&dq=%22Philosophique+Poetica%22&source=bl&ots=GCpzYSaWD7&sig=ACfU3U3O66uQMSyFz4yMX9ex1f6pCMN1hA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjSmb3fyvzjAhVSSX0KHRnyAlUQ6AEwDXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%22Philosophique%20Poetica%22&f=false|title=Complexion Based Discriminations: Global Insights|publisher=Notion Press|year=|isbn=9781643242323|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2019/07/01/world-poetry-conference-poet-in-the-service-of-mankind-philosophique-poetica-and-grand-productions-canada-world-poetry-conference-13th-and-14-th-october-2019/|title=World Poetry Conference: Poet in the service of mankind conference 13th and 14th October 2019|last=Agronsh|first=Agronsh|date=2019-07-01|website=ATUNIS|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldliterature.in/|title=Philosophique Poetica|last=Aggarwal|first=S|date=2019-08-12|website=World Literature India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref>  \n\n==Early life and education==\nBorn in 1955 at [[Ludhiana, Punjab, India|Ludhiana, Punjab]] and grew up at native village Longowal in the Sangrur, Punjab, Anand graduated from Govt. College, Ludhiana, and earned his Masters in English Literature from [[Punjabi University]], [[Patiala]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/07/06/the-interview-of-dr-j-s-anand-with-the-turkish-tv-building-bridges/|title=The Interview of Dr J.S. Anand with the Turkish TV. Building Bridges.|date=2016-07-06|work=Galaktika Poetike \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref> Punjab University, Chandigarh conferred on him degree of Doctor of Philosophy in 2000 for his work on mysticism in the poetry of [[Walt Whitman]] and [[Puran Singh|Prof. Puran Singh]].\n\n==Career==\nAnand began his career as Lecturer in English at [[Gujranwala Guru Nanak Khalsa College|GGN Khalsa College]], Ludhiana. Then he became the Principal at DAV College, Bathinda and served there for 10 years. He co-founded World Foundation for Peace and was National Vice-President of International Human Rights Observatory in 2013 .  In 2016, he was called by the World Union of Poets [Italy]  to serve as the President of the Jury of their 2016 awards.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boloji.com/articles/49111/beyond-life-beyond-death|title=Beyond Life Beyond Death  by Durga Patva|work=Boloji|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\nHe represented India at the Kibatek 39 Poetry Festival organized by the Pablo Naruda Literary Association, Taranto, Italy held in February 2016. He represented India at the World Institute of Peace Nigeria organized World Peace Seminar in Nov. 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnwu.org/index.php/en/our-members/188-chief-advisor-to-the-president-of-the-world-nations-writars-union-in-kazakhstan-on-contemporary-world-literature-3|title=Chief Advisor To The President of the World Nations Writars' Union in Kazakhstan on Contemporary World Literature|last=User|first=Super|website=www.wnwu.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\nDuring his career, he served on the Boards of educational societies including the Senate and Syndicate of [[Punjabi University]], and Board of Studies of [[Guru Kashi University]]. Anand has authored 60 books, published 120 articles, published various national and international anthologies, and has introduced poets by writing Review Articles and Forewords for their books.\n\n==Selected bibliography==\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/2013/20130601/battrib.htm#6|title=A MILLION DESTINIES [Poems]: Post-modern Text traversing the contingent and the transcendent|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781484831342|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18100628-beyond-words-poems|title=Beyond Words [Poems]: A Psycho-Spiritual Odyssey Into the Post-Colonial Mindscape: A Psycho-Spiritual Odyssey Into the Post-Colonial Mindscape|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781484097502|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/Spare_Me_O_Lucifer.html?id=ON6uHAAACAAJ&redir_esc=y|title=Spare me, O Lucifer!: Poems|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Writers Workshop (Rebird)|year=2000|isbn=978-8175956940|location=Kolkata India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.flipkart.com/the-lost-bliss/p/itmecw8fjpzzjbcp|title=THE LOST BLISS|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=The Poetry Society of India Gurgaon|year=2014|isbn=9789383888122|location=Gurgaon|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|title=The Hot Wave (Translation of Punjabi Book Tatti Hawa authored by Om Prakash Gaso)|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Publication Bureau Punjabi University Patiala|year=2014|isbn=9788130202426|location=Patiala|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/trespassers-a-novel/oclc/34851544?loc=|title=The trespassers : A Novel|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Writers Workshop Kolkata|year=1995|isbn=9788171898190|location=Kolkata|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://my.justfiction-edition.com/catalog/details/store/fr/book/978-3-8454-4939-5/the-wolves-of-malwadi?search=the%20wolves%20of%20malwadi|title=The Wolves of Malwadi|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=JustFiction Edition|year=2013|isbn=9783845449395|location=Latvia EU|pages=}}\n*.{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.com/MONSTER-WITHIN-non-fiction-Postmodern-Politico-societal/dp/1490932879|title=The Monster Within: A Postmodern Critique of the Politico-societal living systems (2nd Ed.)|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781490932873|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18208145-confessions-of-a-corpse|title=CONFESSIONS OF A CORPSE: FICTION AT WAR WITH REALITY|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781490516745|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/Metamorphosis-Emerging-Constructs-formation-constructs/dp/3659410586|title=Metamorphosis: Emerging Cultural Constructs And English Proverbs: A study of ancient wisdom in the context of the emerging societal patterns and formation of new constructs|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=LAP LAMBERT Academic Publishing|year=2013|isbn=978-3659410581|location=Saarbrucken Germany|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.in/Bliss-Ultimate-Dr-J-S-Anand/dp/9386242125|title=BLISS: The Ultimate Magic|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9789386242129|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/BELONG-YOU-Spirituality-Dynamics-non-fiction/dp/1490995366|title=I BELONG TO YOU|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781490995366|location=California US|pages=}} \n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.in/Hard-Talk-Discourse-Political-Consciousness/dp/938624232X|title=Hard Talk: A Discourse on Political Consciuosness|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Vishwabharati Research Centre|year=2017|isbn=978-9386242327|location=India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/BROKEN-NARRATIVE-JERNAIL-SINGH-ANAND/dp/B0849T7ZCW/ref=sr_1_6?qid=1585744205&refinements=p_27%3ADr+Jernail+Singh+Anand&s=books&sr=1-6|title=The Broken Narrative|publisher=YAYATI MADAN G GANDHI GROUP OF PUBLICATION|year=2020|isbn=9788194485827|location=Hisar Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/Satanic-Empire-Jernail-Singh-Anand/dp/9383755997|title=The Satanic Empire|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755998|location=Gurgaon Haryana India|pages=}}\n\n===Poems===\n*The Split vision [poetry]\n*Burning Bright [poetry]\n*The Other Passion [poetry]\n*{{Cite book|title=Beyond Life! Beyond Death!|last=Jarnail Singh|first=Anand|publisher=Partridge Publishing|year=2014|isbn=9781482818505|location=|pages=}}\n*Whisper From The Blue [poetry with an Italian poet]\n*{{Cite book|title=VOICES FROM ETERNITY THE GANGES AND THE NILE INCONVERSE|last=Onsy|first=Dr. George|publisher=The Poetry Society of India|year=|isbn=978-93-83888-31-3|location=|pages=}}\n*A study of Walt Whitman's Socio-spiritual and Mystical Concerns and their relevance to the Biorhythm of Post-Modern Indian Society [UGC research project]\n*Poetic Passions, [Anthology of Poetry with a Nigerian Poet.\n\n==Major awards and recognition==\n*Member of the Commission for the International Best Poet Award 2017 of the World Nations Writers Union, Kazakhstan<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnwu.org/index.php/en/|title=High Level Officials of THE WORLD NATION WRITERS UNION OF KAZAKHSTAN (WNWU)|last=Garrido|first=Carlos Hugo|date=2017-10-09|website=World Nation Writers' Union|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-07-12}}</ref>\n*First Ambassador of the World Union of Poets, Italy. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/04/25/world-union-of-poets-celebrates-the-power-of-poetry-aims-to-bring-a-revolution-in-the-consciousness-of-time-issued-by-dr-j-s-anand-ambassador-and-general-director-wup/|title=WORLD UNION OF POETS CELEBRATES THE POWER OF POETRY: AIMS TO BRING A REVOLUTION IN THE CONSCIOUSNESS OF TIME, ISSUED BY Dr. J.S. ANAND, AMBASSADOR AND GENERAL DIRECTOR WUP|last=BORTOLAZZI|first=SILVANO|date=2016-04-25|website=ATUNIS|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n*Chairperson of World Foundation for Peace, and Writers International Foundation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/bathinda/poems-rediscover-island-called-self/216121.html|title=Poems rediscover \u2018island called self\u2019|date=1 April 2016|website=The Tribune}}</ref>\n*Dr Anand  evolved the theory of BIOTEXT in Literary Theory<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2017/10/11/j-s-anands-theory-of-biotext-and-critical-perspectives-on-his-poetic-and-spiritual-creed-first-edition-2016-by-dr-roghayeh-farsi-author-introduction/|title=J.S. Anand\u2019s Theory of Biotext And Critical Perspectives on His Poetic and Spiritual Creed (First Edition, 2016) /  By Dr Roghayeh Farsi (Author, Introduction)|date=2017-10-11|work=Galaktika Poetike  \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref>\n*Cross for Peace for his Lifetime Achievement in the Field of Poetry and Peace by Wolrd Union of Poets. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/11-May-2016/pak-poet-to-get-cross-for-peace-award|title=Pak poet to get Cross for Peace Award|last=Ahmad|first=Israr|date=2016-05-11|website=The Nation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n*2017: Art4peace award by Art4peace Foundation, Hollywood, USA\n*2017: World epitome of leadership award World Institute of Peace, Nigeria\n*2017: Honored with Lord of World Peace and Literature Award, conferred at India World Poetry Festival, held at Ramoji City, Hyderabad 13-14th Oct, 2017\n*Dr M S Randhawa Award for Promotion of Art & Culture of Punjab Conferred\n*2009: Recipient of Penguin Rising Personalities of India Award \n*2008: Best Educationist Award for the outstanding achievements in academics by National and International Compendium in New Delhi\n*Avantika educational excellence award by Sri Rajiv Gandhi Foundation Ratia\n*Founder President, Philosophique Poetica [De-Anand] - A Portal for Poetry, Art, Peace and Philosophy\n\n==Membership and appointments==\n*Member, Syndicate, Punjabi University, Patiala.\n*Fellow, Punjabi University, Patiala\n*Member, Board of Studies, Guru Kashi University, Talwandi Sabo\n*National Vice-president, International Human Rights Observatory [ihro]\n*Patron and Honorary Chief Editor: Symphony International \n*Life Member: [[United Writers' Association|United Writers Association]], Chennai\t\n*Chairman of the International Society of Poets\t\n*Chairman of the Sufi Arts Foundation\t\n*Member of the Association of Indian College Principals\t\n*Patron: Academic Earth Institute of Multi-studies\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anand, Jernail Singh}}\n[[Category:Poets from Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Drsbgarg", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added New Books in Bibliography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jernail_Singh_Anand"}
{"title_page": "Talking Pictures TV", "text_new": "{{short description|British television channel}}\n{{Distinguish|text = the [[BBC]] film and television archival series, [[Talking Pictures (TV series)|Talking Pictures]], or the American radio station Talking Pictures.TV}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2017}}{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox television channel\n|name            = {{unbulleted list|Talking Pictures TV|(TPTV)}}\n|logofile        = TPTV_promotional_logo.png\n|logosize        = 250px\n|logocaption     = Official logo for branding and merchandise\n|logoalt         = \n|launch          = {{start date and age|2015|5|26|df=y}}<ref name=Express/>\n|closed date     = \n|owner           = Talking Pictures TV Ltd\n|picture format  = {{unbulleted list|[[576i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]) [[4:3]] \u2013 main programming<ref name=FAQs/>|[[576i]] (SDTV) [[16:9]] \u2013 commercials, interstitial content<ref name=FAQs/>}}\n|share           = 0.59%\n|share as of     = October 2019\n|share source    = [http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/monthly-viewing-summary/?_s=4 BARB]\n|network         = \n|slogan          = \n|motto           = \n|language        = [[British English]]\n|broadcast area  = [[United Kingdom]], [[Ireland]]\n|affiliates      = \n|headquarters    = [[Watford]], [[Hertfordshire]], England\n|former names    = \n|replaced names  = \n|sister names    = \n|timeshift names = \n|website         = [https://TalkingPicturesTV.co.uk TalkingPicturesTV.co.uk]\n|terr serv 1     = [[Freeview (UK)|Freeview HD]] & [[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]\n|terr chan 1     = channel 81<ref name=FAQs/>\n|sat serv 1      = [[Sky UK|Sky]]\n|sat chan 1      = channel 328<ref name=FAQs/>\n|sat serv 2      = [[Freesat]]\n|sat chan 2      = channel 306<ref name=FAQs/>\n|cable serv 1    = [[Virgin Media]] UK\n|cable chan 1    = channel 445<ref name=FAQs/>\n|iptv serv 1     = [[YouView]]\n|iptv chan 1     = channel 81<ref name=FAQs/>\n}}\n'''Talking Pictures TV''' ('''TPTV''') is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[free-to-air]] vintage-film and nostalgia television channel. It was launched on 26 May 2015 on [[Sky UK|Sky]] channel 343 (Now 328),<ref name=Express>{{cite web|author=Clair Woodward|url=http://www.Express.co.uk/entertainment/tv-radio/577690/Talking-Pictures-TV-Sarah-Cronin-Stanley-interview|title=Talking Pictures TV founder Sarah Cronin-Stanley on the rebirth of Classic British film|website=Express.co.uk|publisher=[[Daily Express]] \u2013 [[Northern & Shell|Express Newspapers]]|date=17 May 2015|accessdate=14 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808011323/https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/577690/Talking-Pictures-TV-Sarah-Cronin-Stanley-interview|archive-date=8 August 2018}}</ref> but later also became available on [[Freeview (UK)|Freeview]], [[Freesat]], and [[Virgin Media]]. It is on air for 24 hours a day and features mainly older British films, both classics and [[B-movie|B-films]],<ref name=\"Barnett\"/> but the schedule also includes some American films, straight-to-video programmes, cinema shorts, and period home movies of British locations.\n\nIn July 2018, Talking Pictures TV had an audience share of 0.50%. As of 2019, it reached an audience share of 0.63%.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/monthly-viewing-summary?_s=4| website=BARB| title=Monthly viewing summary| publisher=barb.co.uk| accessdate=23 October 2019| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125052445/http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/monthly-viewing-summary?_s=4| archive-date=25 January 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nTPTV is a [[family business]], founded by producer/editor Noel Cronin, and run by his daughter Sarah Cronin-Stanley with her husband Neill Stanley.<ref name=\"Barnett\">{{cite news|last=Barnett|first=David|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/long_reads/talking-pictures-tv-black-and-white-television-a7961651.html|title=Talking Pictures TV: The return of black and white television|work=The Independent|date=26 September 2017|accessdate=23 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224052941/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/long_reads/talking-pictures-tv-black-and-white-television-a7961651.html|archive-date=24 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> A wide range of movies from different genres are shown, including [[Horror film|horror]], [[Comedy film|comedy]], [[Drama film|drama]] and [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] films. In-house productions are also shown, as are items from the Cronins' own back catalogue,<ref name=\"Watford Observer\">{{cite web|last=Lacey-Davidson|first=Matty|url=http://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/news/14912346.kings-langley-talking-pictures-tv-channel-shows-old-british-films-and-has-celebrities-like-matt-lucas-barbara-windsor-and-mark-gatiss-talking|title=Talking Pictures TV channel shows old British films and has celebrities like Matt Lucas, Barbara Windsor and Mark Gatiss talking|website=watfordobserver.co.uk|date=17 November 2016|accessdate=11 April 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211193830/https://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/news/14912346.kings-langley-talking-pictures-tv-channel-shows-old-british-films-and-has-celebrities-like-matt-lucas-barbara-windsor-and-mark-gatiss-talking/|archivedate=11 February 2019}}</ref> including Noel's Dandelion Distribution, as well as series from the [[Southern TV]] franchise archive, and early American television shows. Movies are usually copied directly from [[film reel]]s; damaged reels from the catalogue are often replaced by donations, either from online, viewers or available libraries.<ref name=\"SCS podcast\"/>\n\nOne of the aims of the founders was to maintain the history of British cinema; it was said to have been in the making since 2007.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|number=947532030639857668|title=10 years ago my dad had an idea to launch a tvchannel showing only old films,clips of nostalgia,old tv series..Everyone told us we were mad.|author=Talking Pictures TV|date=31 December 2017|accessdate=11 February 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/QL0Kl|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Older movies including those made in black and white were once regularly shown on terrestrial channels, such as BBC and [[Channel 4]],<ref name=\"SCS podcast\"/> but had declined by the 2000s, with only the best known classic films occasionally getting aired. Cronin-Stanley explained to the ''Watford Observer'' in 2016 that \"People were interested in the big titles but he [her father Noel] wanted to save the smaller, more obscure titles, from getting [[Missing film|lost]]\".<ref name=\"Watford Observer\"/> However, television networks rejected their [[Sales pitch|pitches]], unconvinced that it would be of high demand,<ref name=\"SCS podcast\">{{cite interview|last=Cronin-Stanley|first=Sarah|interviewer=Adam Roache|title=The Talking Pictures TV Podcast: March 2019|url=https://www.attaboyclarence.com/the-talking-pictures-tv-podcast/1/3/2019/march-2019|publisher=Adam Roache; [[iTunes]]|location=[[Hertfordshire]]|date=1 March 2019|work=The Talking Pictures TV Podcast|access-date=16 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327233311/https://www.attaboyclarence.com/the-talking-pictures-tv-podcast/1/3/2019/march-2019|archive-date=27 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> so they decided to set up the channel [[Independent station|independently]].<ref name=\"Watford Observer\"/>\n\n===Sponsorship===\n====Merchandise, Renown Pictures====\nFor over 20 years, Cronin-Stanley and Cronin have been patrons to a DVD membership club, The Renown Film Club, for fans of B-film classics.<ref name=Express/> Cronin had worked for [[The Rank Organisation]] and [[Central Office of Information]], and bought the rights to several libraries that owned films that air on TPTV,<ref name=\"Watford Observer\"/> such as much of the [[Southern Television]] library, and originally licensed them out to [[terrestrial channel]]s.<ref name=\"Barnett\"/> Many of the films aired on Talking Pictures TV are available to buy on DVD, often sold as compilations under different genres, through the distributing company,<ref name=Renown>{{cite web|url=https://www.RenownFilms.co.uk|title=Renown Pictures Ltd|website=RenownFilms.co.uk|publisher=Renown Pictures Ltd|accessdate=14 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171014234347/https://www.renownfilms.co.uk/|archive-date=14 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> both online and through the Renown's telephone service. Each DVD set is full of films made between the 1930s and 1960s, and also include special features, such as interviews and history. Other merchandise is also sold on the website, such as mugs, clothing, biographies, and calendars (available to buy in December for the new year), often branded under Talking Pictures TV's name. In spring 2019, Renown released its first CD compilation album named ''Hits From the Flicks'', three CDs of songs from musicals and movies with pop song theme tunes that had aired on the channel.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=Renown_Pictures|title=Full of toe tappers and tunes to whistle along to! Our Hits from the Flicks is out now|number=1120627182919983105|author=Renown Pictures|date=23 April 2019|access-date=23 June 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/FJWuH|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n====The Renown Film Festival====\nSince 2014, the channel's producers created the Renown Film Festival, which celebrates classic British film, featuring guest appearances by actors whose films have been aired, as well as historians, who give interviews; there are also screenings for films that were once considered [[missing film|lost]], and memorabilia available to buy and be autographed by the actors. It occurs annually in February, and tickets are advertised on both TPTV's website and the channel. Actors that have appeared on the guest lists include [[Jess Conrad]] (who reunited with the remaining cast of ''[[The Boys (1962 British film)|The Boys]]'' in 2017),<ref>{{cite tweet|user=TalkingPicsTV|number=926154491866615808|title=20:30 THE BOYS REUNION (2017) PREMIERE the Q&A filmed at Reunion Event held at @ElstreeStudios with #JessConrad #TonyGarnett #DudleySutton|date=2 November 2017|accessdate=11 February 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/FprXf|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> [[Rita Tushingham]],<ref name=\"Renown Festival 2018\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.facebook.com/TalkingPicturesTV/photos/a.651398788327447.1073741830.636949856439007/1194016527399001/?type=3&theater|title=The 4th Renown Festival of Film 2018|website=[[Facebook]]|date=14 December 2017|accessdate=2018-05-22|archive-url=http://archive.today/FQEPe|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> [[Brian Murphy (actor)|Brian Murphy]], [[Melvyn Hayes]], and [[Derren Nesbitt]].<ref name=\"Renown Festival 2018\"/> The festival takes place in [[Hertfordshire]], such as Watersmeet Theatre, [[Rickmansworth]]<ref name=\"Renown Festival 2018\"/> and [[St. Albans]]' The Albans Arena,<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.facebook.com/RenownPicturesOfficial/photos/pb.400096220128387.-2207520000.1552670528./1174597742678227/?type=3&theater|title=The 5th Renown Festival of Film 2019|website=[[Facebook]]|date=28 September 2018|accessdate=15 March 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/iiErg|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> but 2019 will be the first year to have more than one festival in a year; October 2019 will be the Renown Film's 6th Festival of Film at the [[Stockport Plaza]],<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.renownfilms.co.uk/product-category/the-6th-renown-and-talking-pictures-tv-film-festival/|title=The 6th Renown Pictures and Talking Pictures TV Festival Of Film (Stockport)|website=renownfilms.co.uk|accessdate=2019-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190315165940/https://www.renownfilms.co.uk/product-category/the-6th-renown-and-talking-pictures-tv-film-festival/|archive-date=2019-03-15}}</ref> which will also feature special guests, film screenings, and memorabilia.\n\n====Podcast====\nA spin-off [[podcast]] named ''The Talking Pictures TV Podcast'' was announced in December 2018<ref name=\"podcast\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.attaboyclarence.com/blog/5/12/2018/talking-pictures-tv|title=The Official Talking Pictures TV Podcast Announcement!|website=AttaboyClarence.co.uk|date=5 December 2018|accessdate=15 March 2019|first=Adam|last=Roche|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327233259/https://www.attaboyclarence.com/blog/5/12/2018/talking-pictures-tv|archive-date=27 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> by Adam Roche,<ref name=\"Waterman\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.stuartwaterman.com/secret-history-hollywood-podcast-interview-adam-roche/|title=The Chef Who Creates Seven-Hour Podcasts About Horror Movies|website=StuartWaterman.com|first=Stuart|last=Waterman|date=27 August 2015|accessdate=15 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801044408/http://www.stuartwaterman.com/secret-history-hollywood-podcast-interview-adam-roche/|archive-date=1 August 2018}}</ref> the creator of the podcasts ''The Secret History of Hollywood'' and ''Attaboy Clarence'',<ref name=\"Waterman\"/> and began broadcasting on 3 February 2019. Each episode is uploaded monthly to coincide with TPTV's schedule releases and invites the audience to review movies and television programmes that will broadcast on the channel during that month. Its first episode became the most popular podcast in the UK [[iTunes]] chart within roughly five hours.<ref>{{cite podcast|host=Adam Roache|title=Talking Pictures TV Podcast - March 2019|url=https://www.attaboyclarence.com/the-talking-pictures-tv-podcast/1/3/2019/march-2019|website=AttaboyClarence.co.uk|date=3 March 2019|accessdate=15 March 2019|publisher=[[iTunes]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327233311/https://www.attaboyclarence.com/the-talking-pictures-tv-podcast/1/3/2019/march-2019|archivedate=27 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Availability==\nThe channel was initially only available via digital satellite on the Sky platform in the United Kingdom.<ref name=Express/> Since 15 September 2015, it has also been available on Freeview channel 81. It became available on Freesat channel 306 in February 2016,<ref name=FAQs/> and on [[Virgin Media]] on 1 June 2017. On Freeview it was initially broadcast only in [[Standard-definition television|standard definition]] (SDTV) on HD multiplex and could only be received by Freeview HD equipment.<ref name=FAQs>{{cite web|url=https://TalkingPicturesTV.co.uk/faqs/|title=Talking Pictures TV - Frequently Asked Questions|website=TalkingPicturesTV.co.uk|publisher=Talking Pictures TV Ltd|date=|accessdate=14 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016192629/http://talkingpicturestv.co.uk/faqs/|archive-date=16 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> From 30 November 2017, it became available, to those within coverage (90 percent of UK households), on any TV capable of receiving Freeview.<ref>{{citation|journal=[[Radio Times]]|year=2017|volume=25 Nov\u20131 Dec|page=118|title=Talking pictures for all!}}</ref> Since 2 January 2018, it has also been available in the afternoon (12:00\u201318:00) on Freeview Channel 7 in five areas:  Cambridge, Lancashire, Manchester, Oxfordshire and Solent.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://talkingpicturestv.co.uk/talking-pictures-tv-agrees-major-distribution-deal/|title=Talking Pictures TV agrees major distribution deal|website=TalkingPictures.co.uk|accessdate=24 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027004507/http://talkingpicturestv.co.uk/talking-pictures-tv-agrees-major-distribution-deal/|archive-date=27 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The channel has a weekly audience of about 2 million.<ref name=\"Moore\">{{cite news|last=Moore|first=Matthew|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/racist-70s-tv-falls-foul-of-censors-talking-pictures-tv-a-family-at-war-jlxt6ck5n|title=Racist 70s TV falls foul of censors|work=The Times|date=22 February 2018|accessdate=23 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180223110806/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/racist-70s-tv-falls-foul-of-censors-talking-pictures-tv-a-family-at-war-jlxt6ck5n|archive-date=23 February 2018|url-status=live}}{{subscription required}}</ref>\n\n===Controversy===\nThe regulator [[Ofcom]] has warned the channel about the use of [[Racial slur|obsolete racial terms]] in its programming on a handful of occasions,<ref name=\"Moore\"/> including an episode of [[ITV Granada|Granada Television]]'s ''[[A Family at War]]'', originally broadcast in the early 1970s, shown by TPTV in the hour just before the 9pm [[Watershed (broadcasting)|watershed]], and an uncensored interview with [[Joan Turner]] during her appearance on the talk show ''Tell Me Another''.<ref name=\"TMA\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2017/01/09/26584/tv_company_rapped_for_racist_language|title=TV company rapped for racist language|website=chortle.co.uk|publisher=Chortle|date=9 January 2017|accessdate=11 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412083119/http://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2017/01/09/26584/tv_company_rapped_for_racist_language|archive-date=12 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Cronin-Stanley told ''[[The Times]]'' in February 2018: \"Ofcom say we need to advise people before they watch something that it may contain outdated racial stereotyping, but I would say that\u2019s babysitting our audience\".<ref name=\"Moore\"/> However, later in 2018, warning notices had started to appear just before some programmes began, stating, for example, that a programme \"was made between 1975 and 1978, and contains some offensive and discriminatory language which reflects the prevailing attitudes of the time\".\n\n==Broadcast output==\n===Films===\nA list of selected films shown on Talking Pictures TV:\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*''[[A Taste of Honey (film)|A Taste of Honey]]'' (1961 drama starring [[Rita Tushingham]])<ref name=\"Screen Daly\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/talking-pictures-acquires-100-films/5108596.article|title=Talking Pictures acquires 100+ films|author=Michael Rosser|website=screendaly.co.uk|date=19 August 2016|accessdate=12 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025104010/http://www.screendaily.com/news/talking-pictures-acquires-100-films/5108596.article|archive-date=25 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|number=979819306325245957|title=23:35 A TASTE OF HONEY (1961) kitchen sink drama #RitaTushingham #MurrayMelvin #DoraBryan A teen discovers she is pregnant and gets support from an unlikely friend.|date=2018-03-30|accessdate=12 February 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/3fPRI|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*''[[An Alligator Named Daisy]]'' (1955 comedy, starring [[Donald Sinden]])<ref name=\"TPTV schedule March 19-25 2018\"/><ref>{{cite tweet|number=977062400322097152|title=07:40 AN ALLIGATOR NAMED DAISY (1955) comedy #DonaldSinden #DianaDors #JamesRobertsonJustice Peter finds upon his return to England that a tame alligator has been left in his care!|author=Talking Pictures TV|user=talkingpicstv|date=23 March 2018|accessdate=12 February 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/jct6t|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*''[[Au Pair Girls]]'' (1972 comedy, starring [[Gabrielle Drake]])<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|number=810268354984443905|title=00:40 AU PAIR GIRLS (1972) Adult comedy #GabrielleDrake #RichardOSullivan|author=Talking Pictures TV|date=17 December 2016|accessdate=12 February 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/b2kPf|archive-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*''[[Bad Blood (1982 film)|Bad Blood]]'' (1982 thriller, starring [[Jack Thompson (actor)|Jack Thompson]])\n*''[[Ball of Fire]]'' (1941 [[Screwball comedy film|screwball comedy]], starring [[Gary Cooper]])<ref>{{cite tweet|user=TalkingPicsTV|number=831906387412271104|title=Unseen in UK  6pm BALL OF FIRE 1941|author=Talking Pictur