= [[BBC Radio 4]], The Film Programme|access-date=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Screenshot of Talking Pictures TV with Anneke Wills.jpg|right|thumb|Television actress [[Anneke Wills]] sits with film historian Robert Ross in the Cinema Museum during her interview, which aired on the channel in May 2019.<ref name=\"Wills\"/>]] -->\nThe ''Take Two'' series was presented by Elstree historian Morris Bright, and occasionally Robert Ross and/or the channel creators, who interview famous actors whose films and programming is airing on the channel, such as [[Nanette Newman]], [[Angela Douglas]], Rita Tushingham,<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|number=1038049261378826240|title=16:00 RITA TUSHINGHAM (2018) PREMIERE Exclusive interview, hosted by #RobertRoss with the legendary actress.|author=Talking Pictures TV|date=7 September 2018|access-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> [[Sylvia Sims]], [[Michael Craig (actor)|Michael Craig]],<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|number=1008023934598631425|title=19:30 TALKIES: THE MICHAEL CRAIG INTERVIEW (2018) after last months teaser, we present the exclusive interview with the iconic actor #MichaelCraig|author=Talking Pictures TV|date=16 June 2018|access-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> [[Shirley Eaton]], [[Sally Thomsett]], [[Jack Smethurst]], [[Jenny Hanley]], [[Norman Eshley]], [[Valerie Leon]], [[Madeline Smith]], [[Marc Sinden]], and [[Janette Scott]];<ref name=\"WH Times\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.whtimes.co.uk/what-s-on/talking-pictures-tv-to-broadcast-elstree-studios-take-two-interviews-1-4489374|title=Talking Pictures TV to broadcast Elstree Studios' Take Two interviews|website=whtimes.co.uk|publisher=Welwyn Times|date=10 April 2016|access-date=11 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211184618/https://www.whtimes.co.uk/what-s-on/talking-pictures-tv-to-broadcast-elstree-studios-take-two-interviews-1-4489374|archive-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> a few of them recorded [[Station identification|station idents]] for the channel.<ref name=\"Douglas ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=yQN36y1-GNk|title=Angela Douglas endorses Talking Pictures TV|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TptvEndorsements/|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Sinden ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=pAPwzhc9u2M|title=Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year from Marc Sinden|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TptvEndorsements/|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Smethurst ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GVJCSSGCTk0|title=Happy Christmas from Jack Smethurst to All TPTV Fans|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TptvEndorsements/|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Eshley ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=siX5aZV1TXg|title=Norman Eshley endorses Talking Pictures TV|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TptvEndorsements/|archive-date=16 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Syms ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=GX8bEVB7fLo|title=Sylvia Sims Endorsing Talking Pictures TV|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TptvEndorsements/|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Thomsett ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=AH6lJFv6VeE|title=Sally Thomsett wishes a Very Happy Christmas to Everyone Watching Talking Pictures TV|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Leon ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=Lc8nVHGbIJs|title=Valerie Leon - You're Watching the Home of Great Old Movies|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TptvEndorsements/|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Smith ident\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wG5b0XtShFU|title=Merry Christmas from Madeline Smith to Talking Pictures TV viewers|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TPTV_endorsements|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> An interview with ''[[A Family at War]]'' creator John Finch was also aired,<ref name=\"Finch interview\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BGJb3zcMens|title=Talkies: John Finch exclusive interview promo|website=[[YouTube]]|access-date=17 April 2018|archive-url=https://archive.org/details/TPTV_endorsements|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> as well as ''Neil Sean Meets...'', an interviewing series presented by Neil Sean, who has interviewed historians and celebrities of the mid-20th century, such as [[Tommy Steele]],<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|number=673551254312873984|title=7.40pm Neil Sean meets Tommy Steele  Neil Sean sits down with Tommy Steele to discuss his youth @neilsean1 @tvark|date=6 December 2015|access-date=11 February 2019|author=Talking Pictures TV}}</ref> [[Roger Moore]]<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|author=Talking Pictures TV|number=857877257578315776|title=@neilsean1 PREMIERES tomorrow, 15:20 NEIL SEAN MEETS SIR ROGER MOORE **Exclusive** followed at 16:00 VENDETTA FOR THE SAINT (1969) #TPTV|date=28 April 2017|access-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> and [[Eden Kane]]. Interviews from 2018 onwards have been filmed in the [[Cinema Museum (London)|Cinema Museum]] in the wake of the museum's [[foreclosure]] announcement;<ref>{{cite tweet|user=TalkingPicsTV|number=991663139715473408|title=support our favorite London Building and Venue - also our studio occasionally for guest interviews and we are very proud to have their support too|author=Talking Pictures TV|date=2 May 2018|access-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> the interviewees there include [[Mark Lester]], [[George Layton]],<ref>{{cite tweet|user=TalkingPicsTV|author=Talking Pictures TV|number=1128284101474168832|title=Tomorrow (Wed-15-May) at 6pm TALKING PICTURES WITH GEORGE LAYTON (2019)|date=14 May 2019|accessdate=14 May 2019}}</ref> [[Anita Harris]], [[Sid James]]'s daughter Reina,<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|author=Talking Pictures TV|number=1062270629347500032|title=Exclusive interview with Reina James, daughter of dear Sid James coming very soon...|date=13 November 2018|access-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> [[Anneke Wills]],<ref name=\"Wills\">{{cite tweet|author=Talking Pictures TV|user=TalkingPicsTV|title=18:00 TALKING PICTURES WITH ANNEKE WILLS (2019) PREMIERE #AnnekeWills talks to #RobertRoss about her career in this exclusive interview for #TalkingPicturesTV|number=1127951673291358209|date=13 May 2019|accessdate=14 May 2019}}</ref> and [[Peter Butterworth]]'s son Tyler.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|author=Talking Pictures TV|number=1069629892503982081|title=PREMIERE: TALKING PICTURES with TYLER BUTTERWORTH - celebrating his father #PeterButterworth one of Britain's finest comedy actors - Wed-5-Dec at 4:45pm|date=3 December 2018|access-date=11 February 2019}}</ref> Some interviews in the series was later released on a DVD collection named ''Talking Pictures with...''.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|author=Talking Pictures TV|number=1136316861296103425|title=NEW RELEASE on DVD, @Renown_Pictures bring you exclusive Star interviews from #TalkingPicturesTV in a 3-DVD Box Set!|date=5 June 2019|access-date=23 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Themed days===\nThe channel has featured themed days, such as \"An Afternoon with [[Liz Fraser]]\"<ref name=\"Liz Fraser\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MMKbxl74Wtk|title=An Afternoon with Liz Fraser|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=15 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531153458/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MMKbxl74Wtk|archive-date=31 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> (14 August 2016), \"1960s Day\",<ref name=\"1960s Day\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qZ0hDKK4t1c|title=1960s Day|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=12 April 2018}}</ref> \"[[Sophia Loren]] Evening\"<ref name=\"Sophia L Trailer\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mf8Bfe8F9CI|title=Sophia Loren Evening - Official trailer|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=12 April 2018}}</ref> (20 September 2016), \"Music Hall Monday\" (18 January 2016),<ref>{{cite web|title=Music Hall Monday on Talking Pictures TV 18th January 2016|url=https://talkingpicturestv.co.uk/music-hall-monday-talking-pictures-tv/|website=talkingpicturestv.co.uk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623161903/https://talkingpicturestv.co.uk/music-hall-monday-talking-pictures-tv/|archive-date=23 June 2019|accessdate=23 June 2019}}</ref> \"[[Diana Dors]] Day\" (14 May 2017),<ref name=\"Dors\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dm_sFs1KKgg|title=Diana Dors Day - Official trailer|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=12 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528211949/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dm_sFs1KKgg|archive-date=28 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and \"An Afternoon with [[Patricia Dainton]]\" (12 April 2016),<ref name=\"dainton\">{{cite web |title=An Afternoon with Patricia Dainton on Talking Pictures TV... |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gefTXSNVeBU |website=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=23 June 2019}}</ref> in which the actress came out of retirement to provide introductions to her films.  \"[[Laurel and Hardy]] Month\"<ref>{{cite tweet|user=talkingpicstv|author=Talking Pictures TV|number=900997503545376768|title=So next week the Laurel and Hardy season begins on @TalkingPicsTV ... here are the Sept times for all those that have asked.|date=25 August 2017|accessdate=11 February 2019}}</ref> aired their short films and feature-length productions throughout September 2017<ref name=\"L&H Changes\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YBP5Qc3lKFk/|title=Laurel and Hardy Month - official trailer|website=[[YouTube]]|date=2016|accessdate=17 April 2018}}</ref> and their movies continue to be shown.<ref name=\"Barnett\"/>  \"[[Ronald Colman]] Season\"<ref name=\"Colman\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1-42tto0Vzg|title=Ronald Colman Season official trailer|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=12 April 2018}}</ref> occurred throughout November and December 2016, airing movies such as ''[[The Devil to Pay!]]'', ''[[Bulldog Drummond]]'', and ''[[Raffles (1930 film)|Raffles]]''.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://thatwilliampowellsite.wordpress.com/2016/12/02/ronald-colman-season-on-talking-pictures/|title=Ronald Colman Season on Talking Pictures!|website=thatwilliampowellsite.wordpress.com|date=2 December 2016|accessdate=11 February 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211155303/https://thatwilliampowellsite.wordpress.com/2016/12/02/ronald-colman-season-on-talking-pictures/|archivedate=11 February 2019}}</ref> 15 February 2018 was \"[[Sam Kydd]] Day\",<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Talking Pictures TV|user=talkingpicstv|number=963489930499510275|title=SAM KYDD DAY - Thurs-15-Feb|date=13 Feb 2018|accessdate=11 February 2019}}</ref> with showings of a handful of his movies and television appearances, excerpts from his diaries and anecdotes of his life from his son [[Jonathan Kydd (actor)|Jonathan]].<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph\">{{cite news|url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/day-of-movies-devoted-to-sam-kydd-northern-ireland-veteran-of-240-films-36595614.html|title=Day of movies devoted to Sam Kydd - Northern Ireland veteran of 240 films|newspaper=[[Belfast Telegraph]]|date=13 February 2018|accessdate=12 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327233307/https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/day-of-movies-devoted-to-sam-kydd-northern-ireland-veteran-of-240-films-36595614.html|archive-date=27 March 2019}}</ref> 15 March 2019 was \"[[John Gregson]] Day\" which featured movies and television that starred/featured the actor, along with interviews with his family members and remaining cast members of his filmography.<ref name=\"Gregson\">{{cite tweet|author=Talking Pictures TV|user=TalkingPicsTV|number=1104321058423955456|title=Join us for JOHN GREGSON DAY on Fri-15-March - exclusive interviews with John's family, films and programmes to commemorate what would have been his 100th birthday. A wonderful day in tribute to the sorely missed actor.|date=9 March 2019|accessdate=15 March 2019}}</ref> There have also been special guests that host their favourite vintage media that has appeared on the channel, such as [[Danny Baker]]<ref name=\"We Are Cult\">{{citeweb|url=http://wearecult.rocks/danny-baker-takes-over-talking-pictures|title=Danny Baker Takes Over Talking Pictures|website=wearecult.rocks|publisher=We Are Cult|date=6 October 2017|accessdate=12 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412083214/http://wearecult.rocks/danny-baker-takes-over-talking-pictures|archive-date=12 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Vic Reeves]].<ref name=Chortle>{{citeweb|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/features/2017/07/11/37027/vic_reeves_on_his_favourite_classic_movies|title=Vic Reeves on his favourite classic movies|website=chortle.co.uk|date=11 July 2017|accessdate=12 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412083152/http://www.chortle.co.uk/features/2017/07/11/37027/vic_reeves_on_his_favourite_classic_movies|archive-date=12 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\" | {{dagger|alt=Themed days that have not occurred.}}\n| Denotes upcoming themed days that have not yet occurred on the channel.\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Name\n!scope=\"col\"| Date\n!scope=\"col\"| Topic\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n!scope=col class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n!scope=row|''Dial M For Monday''\n|7 December 2015\n|B-movie [[crime film]]s\n|\n|style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>