/> [[1080p]]30 [[H.264/MPEG-4 AVC]] high-profile decoder and encoder<ref name=\"Broadcom-BCM2835-Website\" /> (BCM2837: 1080p60)\n|-\n! Memory (SDRAM)\n| colspan=\"1\" | 256&nbsp;MiB (shared with GPU)\n| colspan=\"4\" | 512&nbsp;MiB (shared with GPU) as of 4 May 2016. Older boards had 256&nbsp;MiB (shared with GPU)<ref name=Aplus512&nbsp;MiB>{{cite web |url =http://uk.farnell.com/raspberry-pi/raspbrry-moda-512m/sbc-raspberry-pi-model-a-512mb/dp/2536236|title=Raspberry Pi Model A+ 512&nbsp;MiB |publisher=[[Premier Farnell|Farnell]] |accessdate=4 May 2016}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"4\" | 1&nbsp;GiB (shared with GPU)\n|1, 2 or 4&nbsp;GiB (shared with GPU)\n| colspan=\"1\" | 512&nbsp;MiB (shared with GPU)\n| colspan=\"4\" | 1&nbsp;GiB (shared with GPU)\n| colspan=\"3\" | 512&nbsp;MiB (shared with GPU)\n|-\n! USB 2.0 ports<ref name=\"VerifiedPeripheralList\">{{cite web|url=http://elinux.org/RaspberryPiBoardVerifiedPeripherals |title=Verified USB Peripherals and SDHC Cards; |publisher=Elinux.org |accessdate=6 May 2012}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1 (direct from BCM2835 chip)\n|1 (direct from BCM2837B0\n\nchip) \n| 2 (via on-board 3-port USB hub<!--; one USB port internally connected to the Ethernet port-->)<ref name=\"SMSC-LAN9512-Website\">{{cite web|url=http://www.smsc.com/index.php?tid=300&pid=135 |title=SMSC LAN9512 Website; |publisher=Smsc.com |accessdate=6 May 2012}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"5\" | 4 (via on-board 5-port USB hub<!--; one USB port internally connected to the Ethernet port-->)<ref name=\"SMSC-LAN9514-specs\">{{cite web|url=http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/9514.pdf |title=Microchip/SMSC LAN9514 data sheet; |publisher=Microchip|accessdate=15 July 2014}}</ref><ref name=B-Plus-Announcement /><ref name=\"LAN7515\">{{cite web|url=http://www.microchip.com/wwwproducts/ProductCompare/LAN7515/LAN9514 |title=ProductCompare LAN7515 LAN9514 |publisher=Microchip|accessdate=14 March 2018}}</ref>\n|2<ref name=ars4>{{Cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2019/06/faster-raspberry-pi-4-promises-desktop-class-performance/|title=The Raspberry Pi 4 brings faster CPU, up to 4&nbsp;GiB of RAM|last=Amadeo|first=Ron|date=24 June 2019|website=Ars Technica|access-date=24 June 2019}}</ref>\n| 1 (direct from BCM2835 chip)*\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1 (direct from BCM2837 chip)*\n| colspan=\"2\" |1 (direct from BCM2837B0 chip)*\n| colspan=\"3\" | 1 Micro-USB (direct from BCM2835 chip)\n|-\n!USB 3.0 ports\n| colspan=\"9\" |0\n|2<ref name=ars4 />\n| colspan=\"8\" |0\n|-\n! Video input\n| colspan=\"10\" | 15-pin [[Mobile Industry Processor Interface|MIPI]] [[camera interface]] ([[Camera Serial Interface|CSI]]) connector, used with the Raspberry Pi camera or Raspberry Pi NoIR camera<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elinux.org/File:Raspi-Model-AB-Mono-2-699x1024.png |title=diagram of Raspberry Pi with CSI camera connector |publisher=Elinux.org |date=2 March 2012 |accessdate=22 June 2012}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"5\" | 2\u00d7 MIPI camera interface (CSI)*<ref name=\"CM-Announcement\" /><ref name=\"CM-Schematic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/hardware/computemodule/RPI-CM-V1_1-SCHEMATIC.pdf|title=Raspberry Pi Compute Module electrical schematic diagram|author=Adams, James|date=3 April 2014|publisher=Raspberry Pi Foundation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530033626/http://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/hardware/computemodule/RPI-CM-V1_1-SCHEMATIC.pdf|archive-date=30 May 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"CM-IO-Board-Schematic\">{{cite web |url=http://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/hardware/computemodule/RPI-CMIO-V1_2-SCHEMATIC.pdf |title=Raspberry Pi Compute Module IO Board electrical schematic diagram |publisher=Raspberry Pi Foundation |date=3 April 2014 |accessdate=22 September 2014 |author=Adams, James|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530033631/http://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/hardware/computemodule/RPI-CMIO-V1_2-SCHEMATIC.pdf|archive-date=30 May 2014}}</ref>\n|None\n| colspan=